We first load the libraries

pacman::p_load(dplyr, magrittr, ggplot2, drake, knitr, ggpubr)

We now load the data.

loadd(dna_kr_data)

Here is a description of columns of dna_kr_data:

knitr::kable(col_names_df)
Columns Description
read_id Read ID
tail_start_ff tailfindrs estimate of poly(A) start site based on fliflop basecalled data
tail_end_ff tailfindrs estimate of poly(A) end site based on fliflop basecalled data
samples_per_nt_ff tailfindrs estimate of read-specific translocation rate in units of samples per nucleotide based on flipflop basecalled data
tail_length_ff tailfindrs estimate of poly(A) tail length based on fliflop basecalled data
tail_start_st tailfindrs estimate of poly(A) start site from data basecalled using standard model
tail_end_st tailfindrs estimate of poly(A) end site from data basecalled using standard model
samples_per_nt_st tailfindrs estimate of read-specific translocation rate in units of samples per nucleotide from data basecalled using standard model
tail_length_st tailfindrs estimate of poly(A) tail length from data basecalled using standard model
read_type Whether the read is poly(A) or poly(T) read
barcode True length of the spikeins
replicate Replicate
file_path Full file path (relevant only for use within Valen lab)
transcript_alignment_start_st Location of tail end as detected by finding the GFP sequencing adjacent to it (based on data basecalled using standard model)
transcript_alignment_start_ff Location of tail end as detected by finding the GFP sequencing adjacent to it (based on data basecalled using flipflop model

tailfindrs tail end estimate vs.tail end estimate obtained by alignment of eGFP

Here, we estimate if the coordinates of the tail end estimated by tailfindr match up with those obtained from the alignment with eGFP sequence.

p <- ggplot(dna_kr_data, aes(x = tail_end_ff, y = transcript_alignment_start_ff)) +
    geom_point(shape = 21, colour = 'black', fill = 'black', size = 2, stroke=0, alpha = 0.1) +
    geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, color="red", linetype = 'dotted', size = 0.7) +
    geom_smooth(method = 'lm',formula = y~x, color="#797979", fullrange = TRUE, se = FALSE, size = 0.5) +
    stat_cor(method = "pearson", label.x = 5000, label.y = 30000) +
    coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0, 40000), ylim = c(0, 40000))

Now we present the same information as histogram.

data <- mutate(dna_kr_data, diff = tail_end_ff - transcript_alignment_start_ff)
p <- ggplot(data, aes(x = diff)) +
  geom_density() + 
  xlab('tail end location estimated by tailfindr - tail end location estimate by eGFP alignment') +
  theme_bw() +
  facet_grid(read_type~., scales="free")
p

Now we present the same information as histogram.

Get the troublesome

df <- dna_kr_data %>% dplyr::filter(transcript_alignment_start_ff > 500 & transcript_alignment_start_ff < 1200) %>% 
  dplyr::filter(tail_end_ff > 1300 & tail_end_ff < 2500) 
save(df, file = file.path(here::here(), 'df.Rda'))
